      "description": "playmode -  - Specifies the method used to playback the output.\n\n locked - This mode locks the output to the local component Timeline. Scrubbing or jumping in the local time will update the output accordingly. When the local timeline loops the output is reset and starts over. The output will be the same for each pass through the local timeline. global - This mode locks the output to the Global beat source. It will follow the Beat  with whose 'Update Global' flag is turned on. local - This mode produces a continuous output regardless of the timeline position.",
      "tooltip": "",
      "help": "",
      "units": "",
